<DOC><DOCNO> AP890724-0270 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-24-89 2116EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-ABCVideo     07-24 0169</FIRST><SECOND>BC-ABC Video,0175</SECOND><HEAD>ABC Video Units Buys Stake in Grocery Billboard Company</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Capital Cities-ABC Video Enterprises Inc. saidMonday it had acquired a minority interest in In-Store AdvertisingInc., which has developed an electronic billboard system that is inabout 1,000 grocery stores.   Capital Cities officials declined to disclose how large aninterest they were buying in the privately-held New York-basedconcern or how much they had invested.   In-Store Advertising has developed electronic billboards thatare installed over store aisles and deliver promotional messagesabout various products to shopers as they are deciding what brandsto buy.   Bruce Maggin, executive vice president of the video enterprisesunit, said the investment continues Capital Cities' strategy ofparticipating ``in a broad spectrum of media activities created bythe new communications technologies.''   He said it would give his company another vehicle for promotingits television and cable programming, and said the billboards couldalso fit into the marketing strategies of national advertisers whoappear on ABC programs.</TEXT></DOC>